\description{
This function estimates pitch using normalized cross-correlation function (NCCF) and
median smoothing, similar to the Kaldi ASR toolkit's pitch tracker
\insertCite{Ghahremani.2014.10.1109/icassp.2014.6854049}{superassp}.

The function uses \code{torchaudio.functional.detect_pitch_frequency} which replaced
the deprecated \code{compute_kaldi_pitch} (removed in torchaudio 2.9+). The algorithm
uses the same NCCF and median smoothing approach as the original Kaldi implementation.

\strong{Note}: This implementation only returns F0 values, not the NCCF (Normalized
Cross-Correlation Function) that was available in the original Kaldi implementation
with \code{compute_kaldi_pitch}. If you need voicing probability, consider using
\code{\link[=rapt]{rapt()}} or \code{\link[=reaper]{reaper()}} which include voicing confidence measures.

All input media formats are supported via torchaudio, including audio extraction
from video files.

The algorithm used is a version of the \link[=rapt]{RAPT} algorithm
that considers voicing also in voiceless frames and conputes a
Normalized Cross Correlation Function (NCCF) that can be used to
estimate the probability of voicing \insertCite{Ghahremani.2014.10.1109/icassp.2014.6854049}{superassp}.

The function calls the \href{https://github.com/pytorch/audio}{torchaudio} \insertCite{yang2021torchaudio}{superassp} library to do the pitch estimates and therefore
relies on it being present in a properly set up python environment to work. Please refer to the \href{https://pytorch.org/audio/main/generated/torchaudio.functional.compute_kaldi_pitch.html}{torchaudio manual} for further information.

